"Myelopathy"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_nr_s13_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"00d3bf",
"children":[
"Spinal cord dysfunction, or myelopathy, can occur because of a lesion arising within the spinal cord (intramedullary) or because of extrinsic compression of the spinal cord."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9a9da7",
"children":[
"Injury to the corticospinal tracts manifests as weakness, hyperreflexia, spasticity, and extensor plantar responses."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d67c74",
"children":[
"Involvement of the distal cord and lower roots (cauda equina syndrome) manifests as lower extremity weakness with decreased muscle tone and areflexia."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1d6d81",
"children":[
"Causes of noncompressive myelopathy include inflammatory or demyelinating lesions, spinal cord infarction, and copper or vitamin B",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"12"
]
},
" deficiency."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_nr_s13_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7468b5",
"children":[
"Spinal cord compression most commonly presents with neck or back pain, followed by weakness, sensory changes, and bowel and bladder dysfunction associated with upper motoneuron signs (weakness, spasticity, hyperreflexia, extensor plantar responses) and occasionally lower motoneuron signs (atrophy, hyporeflexia) at the level of the lesion."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7229e6",
"children":[
"Clues to the cause of compression myelopathy:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0d44aa",
"children":[
"fever — epidural abscess"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a824a3",
"children":[
"anticoagulation — epidural hematoma"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"6e783b",
"children":[
"cancer — metastases"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"84b41c",
"children":[
"trauma — vertebral fracture"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ff90b2",
"children":[
"elderly with chronic back/leg pain — spinal stenosis"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"4a3dd3",
"children":[
"Select MRI of the spine to exclude spinal cord compression in all patients with clinical suspicion of spinal cord disorder. ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"lumbar puncture",
"children":[
"LP"
]
},
" may be beneficial in patients with suspected inflammatory or demyelinating spinal cord lesions."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f3f0a2",
"children":[
"Check methylmalonic acid and homocysteine measurements for patients with borderline vitamin B",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"12"
]
},
" values."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_nr_s13_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b893ea",
"children":[
"Treat spinal cord compression caused by metastatic disease emergently with high-dose glucocorticoids and subsequent surgical decompression followed by radiation for most tumor types."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"dc6b10",
"children":[
"Spinal cord infarction has no treatment."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7dcbca",
"children":[
"For treatment of demyelinating diseases, see Multiple Sclerosis."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b15fd9",
"children":[
"Treat vitamin B",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"12"
]
},
" and copper deficiencies with supplementation."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"94b499",
"children":[
"Direct inflammatory and infectious myelopathy treatment at the underlying disorder."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c2b8a9",
"children":[
"Treat transverse myelitis with IV methylprednisolone."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"defd02",
"children":[
"Spinal cord compression caused by leukemia, lymphoma, myeloma, and germ cell tumors may be treated urgently with radiation therapy rather than surgery."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"3dac40",
"children":[
"Do not use glucocorticoids to treat spinal cord compression caused by infection or hematoma."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
},
